 thanks largely to the efforts of a religious woman, Juliana of Mont Cornillon, who not only popularized the feast, but also wrote key elements of an original office.This volume presents for the first time a complete set of source materials germane to the study of the feast of Corpus Christi. In addition to the multiple versions of the original Latin liturgy, a set of poems in Old French, and their English translations, the book includes complete transcriptions of the music associated with the feast. An introductory essay lays out the historical context for understanding the initiation and reception of the feast.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aCorpus Christi Festival. 7aRELIGION / Holidays / Christian.2bisacsh1 aCorrigan, Vincent, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aCorrigan, Vincent, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRicketts, Peter T., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRicketts, Peter T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWalters, Barbara R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014z978311074526940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780271032849423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780271032849.jpg  a978-3-11-074526-9  Penn State University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014b2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK